Senegal counts votes Senegalese count votes in a presidential election in which the incumbent Macky Sally is highly tipped to win. Nigeria poll death Nigerians await the provisional election results amid deaths from violence arising from a poll considered a two-horse race between the incumbent President Muhammadu Buhari and former Vice-President Atiku Abubakar. Senate president beaten Nigerian Senate President Bukola Saraki loses his bid for re-election. ICJ on Mauritius islands The International Court of Justice gives legal opinion on row between Mauritius and Britain over the Chagos islands. No let-up in Sudan Besieged Sudanese President Omar al-Bashir declares a national state of emergency, dismisses the federal government and sacks all state governors. Anger in Algeria Algerians to hold demonstrations against a fifth mandate for the ailing President Abdulaziz Bouteflika. Egypt hosts summit The European Union and Arab League summit takes place in the Egyptian resort city of Sharm El-Sheikh. Prince visits MoroccoBritain's Prince Harry and Meghan visit till Wednesday Burkina film festival The Pan-African film and television festival continues place in Burkina Faso capital Ouagadougou till Saturday. Mozambique deadly attacks Several people killed in three weekend attacks in Mozambique's northern Cabo Delgado Province. Angola oil talks Angola's state oil firm Sonangol holds a media conference.   President to drum up support for unity government Funding and technology setbacks have delayed mass production of the Kiira EVs.